This paper is about spoken dialog systems, which are typically studied in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a probabilistic framework and uses entropy-based dialog management, which are topics commonly studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach using a dataset, which falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of the proposed approach, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
